Lions’ Suh to Appeal Two-Game NFL Suspension for Kicking Packers Lineman

-- B y   M i c h a e l   B u t e a u
-- 
2011-11-29T21:20:39Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-11-29/lions-suh-to-appeal-two-game-nfl-suspension-for-kicking-packers-lineman.html
Detroit Lions defensive tackle
Ndamukong Suh is appealing the  National Football League ’s two-
game suspension for stomping on an opposing player in a
Nov. 24 loss to the  Green Bay Packers , the NFL said.  Suh’s appeal will be heard and decided by Art Shell, a Hall
of Fame offensive lineman for the Oakland Raiders, this week.
Shell was appointed by the league and players union.  To contact the reporter on this story:
